031/**
032 * Parses a MessagePack stream into a POJO model.
033 *
034 * <h5 class='topic'>Media types</h5>
035 *
036 * Handles <c>Content-Type</c> types:  <bc>octal/msgpack</bc>
037 *
038 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
039 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
040 * </ul>
041 *
042 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
043 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/MessagePackBasics">MessagePack Basics</a>
044
045 * </ul>
046 */
047public class MsgPackParser extends InputStreamParser implements MsgPackMetaProvider {
048
049   /** Default parser, string input encoded as BASE64. */

052      /**
053       * Constructor.
054       *
055       * @param builder The builder for this object.
056       */
057      public Base64(Builder builder) {
058         super(builder.binaryFormat(BinaryFormat.BASE64));
059      }
060   }

604   /** Default parser, string input encoded as spaced-hex. */
605   public static class SpacedHex extends MsgPackParser {
606
607      /**
608       * Constructor.
609       *
610       * @param builder The builder for this object.
611       */
612      public SpacedHex(Builder builder) {
613         super(builder.binaryFormat(BinaryFormat.SPACED_HEX));
614      }
615   }
616
617   /** Default parser, all default settings.*/
618   public static final MsgPackParser DEFAULT = new MsgPackParser(create());
619   /** Default parser, all default settings, string input encoded as spaced-hex.*/
620   public static final MsgPackParser DEFAULT_SPACED_HEX = new SpacedHex(create());
621
622   /** Default parser, all default settings, string input encoded as BASE64.*/
623   public static final MsgPackParser DEFAULT_BASE64 = new Base64(create());

633
634   private final Map<ClassMeta<?>,MsgPackClassMeta> msgPackClassMetas = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
635   private final Map<BeanPropertyMeta,MsgPackBeanPropertyMeta> msgPackBeanPropertyMetas = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
636
637   /**
638    * Constructor.
639    *
640    * @param builder The builder for this object.
641    */
642   public MsgPackParser(Builder builder) {
643      super(builder);
644   }
645
646   @Override /* Overridden from Context */
647   public Builder copy() {
648      return new Builder(this);
649   }
650
651   @Override /* Overridden from Context */
652   public MsgPackParserSession.Builder createSession() {
653      return MsgPackParserSession.create(this);
654   }
655
656   @Override /* Overridden from MsgPackMetaProvider */
657   public MsgPackBeanPropertyMeta getMsgPackBeanPropertyMeta(BeanPropertyMeta bpm) {
658      if (bpm == null)
659         return MsgPackBeanPropertyMeta.DEFAULT;
660      MsgPackBeanPropertyMeta m = msgPackBeanPropertyMetas.get(bpm);
661      if (m == null) {
662         m = new MsgPackBeanPropertyMeta(bpm.getDelegateFor(), this);
663         msgPackBeanPropertyMetas.put(bpm, m);
664      }
665      return m;
666   }
667
668   @Override /* Overridden from MsgPackMetaProvider */
669   public MsgPackClassMeta getMsgPackClassMeta(ClassMeta<?> cm) {
670      MsgPackClassMeta m = msgPackClassMetas.get(cm);
671      if (m == null) {
672         m = new MsgPackClassMeta(cm, this);
673         msgPackClassMetas.put(cm, m);
674      }
675      return m;
676   }
677
678   @Override /* Overridden from Context */
679   public MsgPackParserSession getSession() { return createSession().build(); }
